content.text:
The issue was that the "Sent" folder displayed the recipient list without a space after the "To" prefix (e.g., "ToRecipient" instead of "To Recipient"). This was caused by `MessageHelper.getRecipientDisplayNames` appending the recipient list directly to the prefix returned by `resourceProvider.contactDisplayNamePrefix()` (which is "To:").

I modified `legacy/core/src/main/java/com/fsck/k9/helper/MessageHelper.kt` to append a space character between the prefix and the recipient list.

I verified the fix by creating a new test file `legacy/core/src/test/java/com/fsck/k9/helper/MessageHelperGetRecipientDisplayNamesTest.kt` with a test case reproducing the issue. I confirmed the test failed before the fix and passed after the fix. I then removed the temporary test file.

No existing tests were modified.

Context:
The change is in `MessageHelper.kt`:
```kotlin
// Before
return SpannableStringBuilder(resourceProvider.contactDisplayNamePrefix()).append(recipients)

// After
return SpannableStringBuilder(resourceProvider.contactDisplayNamePrefix()).append(' ').append(recipients)
```

